        "action": {
          "type": "get message",
          "content": "\"Let's solve this step by step.\n\nWe have:\n- 20 family members\n- 32 pets total\n- Each member has at least 1 pet\n- We want to find the maximum number of members who can have exactly 3 pets\n\nTo maximize the number of members with 3 pets, we should minimize the number of pets for the remaining members. Since each member must have at least 1 pet, the minimum is 1 pet.\n\nLet's say x members have 3 pets, and (20-x) members have 1 pet (the minimum).\n\nTotal pets = 3x + 1(20-x) = 3x + 20 - x = 2x + 20\n\nWe know total pets = 32, so:\n2x + 20 = 32\n2x = 12\nx = 6\n\nSo 6 members can have 3 pets, and 14 members have 1 pet each.\n\nLet's verify: 6 × 3 + 14 × 1 = 18 + 14 = 32 ✓\n\nThe maximum number of members that can have 3 pets is 6.\"",
